    {
      "id": "5a21debbcc9b9a3d66d68ce6ac16401af30a7237",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 808,
        "name": "Shaun Tancheff",
        "email": "shaun.tancheff@hpe.com",
        "username": "stancheff"
      },
      "date": "2020-04-21 20:04:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nWell the patches apply but the build fails:\n   --with-linux=/usr/src/linux-4.12.14-197.37\n\n/home/shaun/lustre-release/ldiskfs/xattr.c:330:46: error: macro \"ldiskfs_iget\" requires 3 arguments, but only 2 given\n  ea_inode = ldiskfs_iget(parent->i_sb, ea_ino);\n                                              ^\n/home/shaun/lustre-release/ldiskfs/xattr.c:330:13: error: ‘ldiskfs_iget’ undeclared (first use in this function); did you mean ‘__ldiskfs_iget’?\n  ea_inode = ldiskfs_iget(parent->i_sb, ea_ino);\n             ^~~~~~~~~~~~\n             __ldiskfs_iget",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "2eff0f23f62e8106cd2d84e5bb544e3dc25302b7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 808,
        "name": "Shaun Tancheff",
        "email": "shaun.tancheff@hpe.com",
        "username": "stancheff"
      },
      "date": "2020-04-21 20:32:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nSadly the patches do not stack using --with-linux=/usr/src/linux-4.12.14-150.22\n\nApplying patch patches/suse15/ext4-attach-jinode-in-writepages.patch\n1 out of 3 hunks FAILED\nPatch patches/suse15/ext4-attach-jinode-in-writepages.patch does not apply (enforce with -f)\nmake[2]: *** [autoMakefile:624: sources] Error 1",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "a069ca4947e264e7b4f8c333fce291bbd2b167f2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 805,
        "name": "Neil Brown",
        "email": "neil@brown.name",
        "username": "neilbrown"
      },
      "date": "2020-04-30 01:45:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Sadly the patches do not stack using --with-linux=/usr/src/linux-4.12.14-150.22\n\nSadly 4.12.14-150.22 is an ancient release - June last year.\nrpm-4.12.14-150.47 seems to be the last SLE15 release before it entered LTSS.\n\nWhy are you still using 4.12.14-150.22 ??\nWhat is the policy on supporting older releases?\nIt would actually suit me to always support the first release of any given SLE service pack as that it what we build KMPs against for the life of the SP.\n\nSo I can make it work for other releases, but I'd like to know what the goal is.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "426f69f039c7cccccf56b4f6bd227a60456f34fb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 808,
        "name": "Shaun Tancheff",
        "email": "shaun.tancheff@hpe.com",
        "username": "stancheff"
      },
      "date": "2020-04-30 03:04:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nRight now 4.12.14-197.7 is still pretty active here same problem as 150 though.\n\nSince this is relatively current with CLE7 I suspect we will be supporting for quite a while though I don't know the official policy.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
